    </div>

    <style>
      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        section div[style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr"] {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
          gap: 32px !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- BOND AMOUNTS -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">How Much Does a Lincoln County Bail Bond Cost?</h2>

      <p style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 18px; padding: 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>Lincoln County bail bond costs are based on the charge and the bail amount set by the judge. In Oklahoma, bail bond premiums are a percentage of the total bail amount. Common bail amounts in Lincoln County include approximately $500-$1,500 for misdemeanor DUI, $500-$5,000 for most misdemeanors, and $5,000-$100,000+ for felony charges. Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates and flexible payment plans.</strong></p>

      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Lincoln County uses a bail schedule for common offenses, which allows many misdemeanor defendants to post bond immediately after booking without waiting for a judge. For felony charges, a bond hearing before a Lincoln County District Court judge is typically required. Bail amounts in felony cases depend on the severity of the charge, criminal history, flight risk, and community ties.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">If the defendant does not post bail within the first 24 hours, they must appear before a judge who will formally set the bond amount. This first appearance can be conducted in person at the Lincoln County Courthouse or via telephone. Angel Bail Bonds can begin the paperwork process over the phone before arriving at the jail, which means we can post the bond faster once we get to Chandler.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Lincoln County Jail is one of the larger county facilities in central Oklahoma with a 128-inmate capacity. Because the jail shares a complex with the courthouse at 811 Manvel Ave in Chandler, bond hearings and arraignments can be conducted quickly — often by video from the jail itself.</p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">What Payment Methods Does Angel Bail Bonds Accept for Lincoln County Bonds?</h3>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 12px 16px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;"><strong>Angel Bail Bonds accepts cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, and Venmo for Lincoln County bail bonds. Financing is available for qualifying clients. We can process payments over the phone, making it possible to start the release process before meeting in person. There are no hidden fees.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT LINCOLN COUNTY — unique local content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Where Is Lincoln County Jail and How Do I Get There?</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 12px 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>Lincoln County Jail is located at 811 Manvel Avenue, Suite 14, Chandler, OK 74834, in the same complex as the Lincoln County Courthouse. Chandler is approximately 50 miles south of Stillwater along SH-18, and about 50 miles northeast of Oklahoma City. The Lincoln County Sheriff's Office, headed by Sheriff Charlie Dougherty, operates the 128-bed facility. The jail phone number is (405) 258-1191 ext. 294.</strong></p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Lincoln County is located in central Oklahoma, directly south of Payne County. With a population of roughly 34,000, the county covers approximately 966 square miles of rolling terrain between Oklahoma City and Tulsa. The county seat is Chandler, a historic Route 66 town along SH-66 about 50 miles south of Stillwater. Lincoln County was established in 1891 and named for President Abraham Lincoln.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">The Turner Turnpike (Interstate 44) runs through the northern part of Lincoln County near Stroud, making turnpike-related arrests common in the Lincoln County system. Whether someone is arrested on I-44, pulled over in Prague, or picked up in Meeker, all Lincoln County arrests are processed through the jail in Chandler. Angel Bail Bonds regularly handles turnpike arrests and can begin the bail process by phone before even arriving at the facility.</p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">What Communities Does Angel Bail Bonds Serve in Lincoln County?</h3>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Angel Bail Bonds serves every community in Lincoln County. In addition to Chandler, we regularly post bonds for residents of Stroud (located along I-44 between OKC and Tulsa), Prague (southeastern Lincoln County, hometown of Jim Thorpe), Meeker (southern Lincoln County), Davenport (along SH-18 between Chandler and Stillwater), Carney, Agra, Sparks, Warwick, and Tryon. All arrests from these communities are processed at the Lincoln County Jail in Chandler.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Lincoln County Communities We Serve</h3>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 14px;">
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Chandler</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Stroud</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Prague</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Meeker</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Davenport</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Carney</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Agra</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Sparks</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Warwick</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Tryon</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COURTHOUSE + COURT INFO -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Lincoln County Courthouse and Court Appearance Information</h2>

      <p style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 18px; padding: 16px; background: #f0f7ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 4px;"><strong>The Lincoln County Courthouse is located at 811 Manvel Ave, Chandler, OK 74834 — in the same complex as the county jail. The Court Clerk is Cindy Kirby, reachable at (405) 258-1264. Office hours are Monday through Friday, 8:30 AM to 4:30 PM. All Lincoln County criminal cases are heard in the Lincoln County District Court. Court dockets are available at oscn.net.</strong></p>

      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">After posting bail and being released from Lincoln County Jail, the defendant must appear at all scheduled court hearings at the Lincoln County Courthouse. Failure to appear will result in forfeiture of the bond, a bench warrant, and additional criminal charges. Angel Bail Bonds will remind you of upcoming court dates and help ensure you understand your obligations.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Arraignments in Lincoln County typically occur within 24 hours of arrest for defendants who have not posted bail. During the arraignment, the judge informs the defendant of the charges and formally sets the bail amount. For misdemeanor cases, bail is often available through a preset bond schedule, meaning the defendant can bond out immediately after booking. Felony cases may require a separate bond hearing. Because the courthouse and jail share the same complex, hearings can be conducted via video from the jail.</p>
      </div>

      <table style="width: 100%; font-size: 0.9rem; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 16px; background: white; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
        <tr style="background: var(--navy);">
          <td colspan="2" style="padding: 12px 16px; color: white; font-weight: 700;">Lincoln County Courthouse Quick Reference</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600; width: 130px;">Address</td>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-700);">811 Manvel Ave, Chandler, OK 74834</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600;">Court Clerk</td>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-700);">Cindy Kirby · <a href="tel:+14052581264" style="color: var(--blue);">(405) 258-1264</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600;">Office Hours</td>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-700);">Mon-Fri 8:30 AM - 4:30 PM</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600;">Mailing</td>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-700);">P.O. Box 307, Chandler, OK 74834</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600;">Dockets</td>
          <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: var(--slate-700);"><a href="https://www.oscn.net/dockets/" style="color: var(--blue);" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oscn.net/dockets</a></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
